{"type":"message","id":"9a0b2cad","parentId":"e0abacc2","timestamp":"2026-02-20T09:14:47.884Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ah, the cron job is failing with \"gateway timeout after 60000ms\". This is a cron issue, not the subagent task. The user triggered the cron task but it timed out.\n\nThe issue is that the cron job is trying to run but timing out. Let me check if there's an issue with how the cron job is configured, or maybe the gateway is still having issues.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully - the user asked to \"重发定时任务我看看\" (resend the scheduled task to see), which means they wanted to manually trigger the cron job again. But the cron tool is timing out.\n\nThis could be because:\n1. The gateway is overloaded or stuck\n2. There's an issue with the cron job itself\n\nLet me try a different approach - use the sessions_spawn to run the task directly, which we've already done successfully earlier today. The task completed successfully and sent an email.\n\nBut the user wants to see if the cron configuration is fixed. The problem is the cron run command keeps timing out. Let me check if the gateway needs to be restarted again.","thinkingSignature":"5fecf53f4ca67fa7d648c363047be8f303a0073d69f3241cc95f19b022550952"},{"type":"text","text":"又是 gateway 超时。让我重启一下再试：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r9ll5fcf28z9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"systemctl --user restart openclaw-gateway 2>&1; sleep 3; echo \"done\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":28,"output":291,"cacheRead":7823,"cacheWrite":45237,"totalTokens":53379,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771578876051}}
